                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, May 25: Standard Chartered Plcs Rs 2,760-crore public offer of Indian depository receipts got subscribed just 5 per cent on the opening day of the issue today. The issue got total bids for 1.1 crore receipts against 20.4 crore receipts on offer, thereby getting subscribed 0.05 times. Standard Chartered has come out with a public offer of 24 crore IDRs.                             
	 New Delhi, May 25: Reliance Industries chief Mukesh Ambani has capped his salary for the second straight year at Rs 15 crore against Rs 39.36 crore that he is eligible to draw, while the rest of the RIL top brass got a pay hike in fiscal 2010. The remuneration for 2009-10 fiscal to Mukesh Ambani is still higher than any other director of Reliance Industries.                            
	 Mumbai, May 25: Tata Tea has posted a 44.28 per cent decline in its consolidated net profit at Rs 390 crore for the year ended March 31, 2010 compared with Rs 700 crore in the year-ago period. However, total operating income went up 19 per cent to Rs 5,821 crore during the fiscal from Rs 4,874 crore in the year-ago period.                             
	 Mumbai, May 25: Marico today announced the acquisition of the aesthetics business of Singapore-based Derma Rx Asia Pacific (Derma Rx) through its wholly-owned subsidiary Kaya Limited.                             
	 Mumbai, May 25: Realty firm Lodha Group today bagged a 25,000-sq metre plot at Wadala here for Rs 4,050 crore, which is termed as the costliest deal in the city so far.
                                                                                                                          
